tyle="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and that was intended to offset the deteriorating capital base because of the non-core business.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q513 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Chair:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> You were already well aware of the things that Moody’s might find and that the PRA were finding, but you felt that that was consistent with being able to say that your balance sheet remained strong?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Barry Tootell</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: Yes, but there was nothing for Moody’s to find. We had been very open with the regulator and with rating agencies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in terms of the asset quality of the balance sheet. Moody’s assessment of our credit rating was based upon their look-forward basis of assessing that asset credit quality and the means by which they thought we would accommodate that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and their judgment was a multi-notch downgrade of the business way beyond that which we anticipated.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12