ew Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">No, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I understand that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">B</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ut clearly there was a problem</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> though, right?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Barry Tootell</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">here was a problem that we were addressing. This is the requirement for us to increase our capital still further, which we were doing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by divesting other aspects of our business within the broader Co-operative Banking Group and redeploying it into the bank to face off against what we saw as the deteriorating capital base in the underlying non-core business.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q517 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Mr Newmark:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Who were your accountants at the time?</spa