Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in overall terms. Peter Marks attended each </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> meeting as the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">chief executive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and, therefore, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">primary officer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. H</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e was not a member of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> itself but he attended these </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> meetings. So, yes, he was a chairman of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">risk management committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but I would regard the primary decision-making forum as being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="m