12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">overnment and a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">executive committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> being the Government and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> being the Parliament. Do you think that is a fair way to sum this up?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Barry Tootell</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: If we are talking about the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">executive committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, yes, that would be a fair way to sum up the way in which the broader </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">roup or the trading aspects of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> operated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but not its oversight over the banking business.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q631 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Mr McFadden:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Again, going back to Verde, would this have been a recommendation made by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">executive committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">then goes to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for approval</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> or would it have been something that originated within the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">board</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as being a good thing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for the group to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> do</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span 