xt-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">John Thurso:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> I am having difficulty with this. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">You are no longer there, but the Co-op Bank—something a lot of us would like to support, both in concept and reality—is now likely to end up as a listed company</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with 30% of its equity owned by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Co-op</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> board. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It is going to have to be run in the way of companies listed on the market with all the good and bad that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">come</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">probably set back the concept of mutuality in finance </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">some considerable time.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am looking to see what could or could not have been avoided in the corporate governance structures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and you are telling me</span><span sty